# Backend Architecture Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the steps to build the separate backend project, structurally completely independent from `taskflow-app` (frontend) and future mobile app, inside `d:\Developments\College Project\taskflow-backend`.

## User Review Required
Please review the proposed backend directory structure and the initial base dependencies. Once approved, I will functionally create these folders and files. No changes will be made to the frontend or UI.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Directory Structure (`taskflow-backend`)
I will execute commands to create the following directory tree:
```
taskflow-backend/
├── src/
│   ├── controllers/    # Route handlers
│   ├── services/       # Business logic layer
│   ├── models/         # Database queries
│   ├── middleware/     # Auth, rate-limiter, errorHandler
│   ├── routes/         # Express routers
│   ├── utils/          # Helpers (jwt, logger, etc.)
│   └── app.js          # Express app configuration
├── migrations/         # SQL migration files
├── seeds/              # Dev seed data
├── tests/              # Jest test files
├── .env.example        # Environment variables template
├── .gitignore          # Git ignore rules
└── server.js           # Entry point and Server startup
```

### 2. Base Dependency Initialization
I will initialize an NPM project and install the base packages required to set up the foundation:
- **Core:** `express`, `cors`, `dotenv`, `helmet`, `morgan`
- **Database:** `mysql2`
- **Dev:** `nodemon` 

### 3. File Creation (Boilerplate)
I will write simple, foundational setup code (non-complex, as requested) to get the server ready:
#### [NEW] `taskflow-backend/server.js` (Entry Point, attaches to port, handles graceful shutdown)
#### [NEW] `taskflow-backend/src/app.js` (Express configuration with core middlewares like CORS, Helmet, JSON parsing)
#### [NEW] `taskflow-backend/.env.example` (Template variables)

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
1. I will use the `run_command` tool to initialize the folders.
2. I will verify that `npm init -y` and `npm install` complete successfully.
3. I will start the server momentarily to verify that the placeholder app runs successfully without errors on a defined port (e.g., `5000`).
